With the ban on the sale of alcohol you may find yourself rummaging through those dusty forgotten bottles in the back of the booze cupboard, as I did, and came upon a couple of bottles of limoncello made with last season's lemons. Happiness. Add a sparkle with fresh lemon or lime, soda or sparkling water, ice and a splash of vodka if you fancy. Makes: 1 jug Ingredients: 250ml (1 cup) limoncello Splash of vodka, if using Zest and juice of 3 large lemons or 6 limes 1 litre ice-cold soda or sparkling water Ice cubes and lemon slices to garnish Method: